      },
      "time": "~35s",
      "narrative": "- In VS Code, connect the agent to the right IQs.\n- The local proof of concept used simulated records.\n- This version can reach real enterprise evidence with visible guardrails on tool calls.\n- That is the difference between a good demo and a system the business can trust.",
      "demo_actions": "Open the agent project in VS Code. Show configuration for IQs, tool access, and policy controls.",
      "screenshot": ".cutready/screenshots/20260622_142540_vlcsnap-2026-06-22-14h25m35s396.png"
    },
    {
      "locked": false,
      "locks": {
        "time": false,
        "narrative": false,
        "demo_actions": false,
        "screenshot": false,
        "visual": false,
        "design_plan": false
      },
      "time": "~40s",
      "narrative": "- Name the sources clearly.\n- Work IQ brings in email and Microsoft 365 context.\n- Foundry IQ brings indexed contracts.\n- Fabric IQ brings structured invoice data.\n- Web IQ can add current outside financial context when needed.",
      "demo_actions": "Open the toolbox or connected data sources and point out the key IQs that support invoice assurance.",
      "screenshot": ".cutready/screenshots/20260622_142437_vlcsnap-2026-06-22-14h24m33s324.png"
    },
    {
      "locked": false,
      "locks": {
        "time": false,
        "narrative": false,
        "demo_actions": false,
        "screenshot": false,
        "visual": false,
        "design_plan": false
      },
      "time": "~30s",
      "narrative": "- Once those connections are in place, deploy the agent as a hosted agent in Foundry.\n- Now we have a managed runtime with isolation and a clear execution path we can inspect.\n- The idea is the same as the local build.\n- The operating model is now enterprise-ready.",
      "demo_actions": "Deploy the agent in Foundry. Show hosted agent setup, cloud isolation cues, and a simple execution.",
      "screenshot": ".cutready/screenshots/20260622_142605_vlcsnap-2026-06-22-14h25m58s345.png"
    },
    {
      "locked": false,
      "locks": {
